The inclusion of Cyrus the Great isn't only a good tie-in, it's a great way to lend legitimacy to this article, which admittedly I was a bit skeptical of at first. But, the historical texts are actually put together pretty believably, and written extremely well content-wise. This could have been easily dismissed as a cliche  but the history behind it definitely lends interest beyond that.

